t-term%2C%20but%20then%20something%20unexpected%20happened%3A%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAll%20in%20all%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmultigenerational-living-pros-cons-parents-health-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emy%20parents%20lived%20with%20us%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20and%20off%20over%20the%20course%20of%20two%20years%2C%20and%20while%20there%20were%20some%20challenges%20during%20that%20time%20together%2C%20we%20both%20see%20it%20as%20a%20huge%20gift.%20I've%20even%20begged%20them%20to%20move%20back%20in%20(more%20on%20that%20later).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221652326b-bb8e-4743-94bf-520630d5d0cd%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EThey%20provided%20me%20with%20help%20at%20a%20crucial%20time%20in%20my%20life%20after%20my%205th%20child%20was%20born%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20first%20time%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpeople-call-my-family-nontraditional-i-disagree-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emy%20parents%20moved%20in%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20they%20stayed%20for%20only%20three%20months.%20They%20moved%20in%20shortly%20after%20school%20had%20started%20for%20my%20four%20oldest%20children%2C%20and%20having%20them%20there%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20a%20huge%20blessing%20in%20disguise.%20Although%20they%20both%20worked%20full-time%2C%20my%20mom%20was%20around%20in%20the%20late%20afternoons%20and%20evenings%20to%20help%20me%20with%20the%20kids%20and%20their%20activities.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETheir%20move%20coincided%20with%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-wont-allow-my-son-to-play-football-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Efall%20sports%20season%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20which%20worked%20out%20perfectly%20for%20me.%20I%20had%20no%20idea%20how%20challenging%20it%20would%20be%20to%20have%20a%20newborn%20and%20four%20other%20kids%20in%20sports%20and%20activities%2C%20so%20my%20mom's%20helping%20hand%20felt%20like%20a%20lifesaver.%20She%20also%20frequently%20folded%20endless%20loads%20of%20laundry%20for%20me%20in%20the%20morning%20and%20even%20would%20sometimes%20take%20the%20baby's%20first%20morning%20feeding%20while%20I%20slept%20in%20longer%2C%20since%20she%20tended%20to%20wake%20up%20early.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20fact%2C%20my%20daughter's%20first%20smiles%20happened%20on%20the%20couch%20with%20her%20grandma.%20I%20woke%20up%20to%20pictures%20she%20texted%20me%20of%20my%20baby%20breaking%20into%20a%20huge%20smile%2C%20and%20those%20are%20precious%20memories%20for%20both%20of%20us.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225d7ebb2d-d12e-479a-a793-fa4bef6cb6d4%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20pandemic%20affected%20my%20parents'%20plans%20to%20build%20a%20home%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20parents'%20first%20move%20in%20with%20us%20was%20temporary%3B%20they%20closed%20on%20a%20condo%20and%20moved%20into%20it%20shortly%20before%20Christmas.%20I%20felt%20stronger%20and%20more%20rested%20by%20the%20end%20of%20their%20time%20with%20us%2C%20and%20I%20had%20settled%20into%20a%20more%20comfortable%20groove%20as%20a%20mom%20of%20five%20kids.%20My%20parents%20had%20arrived%20at%20the%20exact%20time%20I%20needed%20more%20help%2C%20and%20it%20felt%20like%20everything%20had%20worked%20out%20perfectly%20for%20both%20of%20us.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%20when%20the%20condo%20they%20bought%20didn't%20work%20out%20and%20they%20wanted%20to%20sell%20again%2C%20roughly%20a%20year%20later%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20did%20not%20hesitate%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhappy-moved-back-in-with-my-parents-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewelcome%20them%20back%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20plan%20was%20for%20them%20to%20live%20with%20us%20for%20about%20a%20month%20or%20two%20until%20they%20built%20a%20new%20home.%20However%2C%20then%20the%20pandemic%20hit.%20The%20world%20essentially%20shut%20down%2C%20and%20everything%20from%20labor%20to%20materials%20was%20scarce%20and%20expensive%2C%20or%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20nonexistent%20altogether.%20Construction%20obviously%20became%20massively%20delayed%2C%20and%20the%20months%20soon%20stretched%20out.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20time%20around%2C%20I%20was%20out%20of%20the%20newborn%20fog%2C%20the%20kids%20were%20older%2C%20and%20I%20was%20working%20more%2C%20so%20we%20did%20encounter%20a%20few%20challenges.%20For%20instance%2C%20it%20was%20difficult%20for%20me%20to%20find%20alone%20time%20to%20work%20or%20decompress.%20I'd%20been%20accustomed%20to%20waking%20up%20early%20to%20work%20and%20having%20my%20coffee%20in%20silence%20before%20the%20kids%20were%20up%2C%20but%20I%20soon%20found%20that%20my%20mom%20liked%20to%20wake%20up%20early%20too%20%E2%80%94%20and%20she%20was%20a%20talker%2C%20even%20at%205%20a.m..%20I%20also%20sometimes%20struggled%20with%20feeling%20like%20I%20was%20doing%20more%20cooking%20and%20cleaning%20while%20she%20got%20to%20play%20with%20the%20kids.%20But%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20my%20parents%20decided%20to%20generously%20give%20us%20%24500%20a%20month%20in%20%26quot%3Brent%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20to%20help%20offset%20their%20meager%20food%20costs.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20were%20also%20immeasurable%20benefits%20to%20my%20parents%20living%20there.%20Our%20baby%20essentially%20grew%20up%20with%20her%20%26quot%3BPapa%2C%26quot%3B%20spending%20nearly%20every%20morning%20snuggling%20and%20watching%20her%20favorite%20cartoons%20with%20him%3B%20my%20son%20played%20endless%20games%20of%20basketball%20with%20my%20dad%20in%20the%20driveway%2C%20and%20we%20all%20ate%20dinner%20together%20every%20night.%20My%20mom%20also%20happened%20to%20do%20the%20dishes%20like%20a%20pro%2C%20so%20that%20was%20a%20definite%20bonus.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22353c2cd8-7d43-4f04-b30d-5628661608be%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EI'd%20welcome%20my%20parents%20back%20with%20open%20arms%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEventually%2C%20the%20following%20year%2C%20with%20construction%20in%20a%20standstill%20because%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20my%20parents%20decided%20to%20move%20into%20an%20apartment%20while%20they%20figured%20out%20their%20next%20steps.%20They%20felt%20our%20time%20together%20had%20come%20to%20a%20natural%20close%2C%20and%20space%20would%20be%20best%20for%20everyone.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20I%20agreed%2C%20but%20now%2C%20looking%20back%2C%20I%20can%20only%20say%20that%20I%20would%20welcome%20them%20back%20in%20a%20heartbeat.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20kids%20got%20the%20gift%20of%20having%20their%20grandparents%20around%2C%20I%20had%20a%20helping%20hand%20with%20dreaded%20chores%20like%20laundry%20and%20dishes%2C%20and%20it%20felt%20like%20we%20were%20constantly%20making%20memories%20together.%20Plus%2C%20if%20I'm%20being%20honest%2C%20I%20can%20clearly%20see%20how%20much%20an%20extra%20%24500%20a%20month%20would%20help%20us%20right%20now%2C%20especially%20when%20I'm%20struggling%20to%20make%20ends%20meet.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIronically%2C%20my%20parents%20have%20decided%20to%20sell%20the%20house%20they%20built%20yet%20again%20and%20have%20once%20again%20moved%20down%20to%20a%20basement.%20This%20time%2C%20however%2C%20they%20chose%20to%20live%20with%20my%20younger%20sister%20instead%20of%20us.%20I%20have%20begged%20them%20to%20move%20back%20in%20with%20us%2C%20arguing%20that%20they%20could%20travel%20or%20buy%20a%20vacation%20home%20and%20come%20and%20go%20as%20they%20please%20from%20our%20basement.%20However%2C%20so%20far%2C%20they%20have%20refused%20my%20pleas.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMaybe%20