Steve%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EJoe%2C%20I%20read%20your%20piece%20with%20great%20intrigue%2C%20but%20I%20must%20say%20the%20old-school%20thinking%20in%20me%20shudders%20when%20Wall%20Street%20firms%20start%20using%20non-traditional%20metrics%20to%20justify%20a%20rally%20%E2%80%94%20as%20both%20Goldman%20and%20Morgan%20Stanley%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConversely%2C%20a%20tried-and-true%20valuation%20indicator%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Shiller%20P%2FE%20ratio%2C%20which%20dates%20back%20to%20the%2019th%20century%20%E2%80%94%20is%20at%20a%20frighteningly%20high%20level%2C%20above%2040.%20It%20was%20higher%20during%20the%20dot-com%20bubble.%20Ignore%20the%20ratio%20at%20your%20peril%3A%20it%20accurately%20projected%20market%20tops%20in%201929%20and%201999-2000%2C%20and%20also%20flashed%20red%20before%20the%20mid-2000s%20housing%20crash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJoe%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20agree%20the%20Shiller%20P%2FE%20is%20alarming!%20But%20I%20also%20think%20it's%20failing%20to%20account%20for%20a%20few%20key%20attributes%20of%20the%20companies%20leading%20the%20market.%20If%20you%20adjust%20valuation%20measures%20for%20profit%20growth%2C%20cash%20flow%2C%20and%20profit%20margins%2C%20parallels%20to%20the%20dot-com%20era%20weaken%20significantly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20yes%2C%20Wall%20Street%20loves%20to%20create%20new%20metrics%20to%20paint%20the%20story%20they%20want%20to%20tell.%20But%20in%20this%20case%2C%20the%20adjustments%20paint%20a%20more%20accurate%20and%20modern%20picture%20of%20corporate%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cu%3ECompany%20quality%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJoe%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20companies%20driving%20the%20AI%20revolution%20are%20just%20stronger.%20On%20average%2C%20they%20have%20better%20cash%20flow%2C%20operate%20more%20efficiently%2C%20and%20are%20more%20profitable.%20That's%20certainly%20the%20case%20for%20the%20absolute%20biggest%20names%20responsible%20for%20moving%20the%20market%3A%20Nvidia%2C%20Microsoft%2