s%20were%20down%20to%20%241%2C166.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20seems%20like%20fewer%20people%20are%20visiting%20the%20city%20from%20abroad.%20I%20think%20domestic%20tourism%20is%20down%2C%20too%2C%20because%20some%20people%20can't%20afford%20to%20travel.%20I've%20seen%20reports%20here%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.colliers.com%2Fen%2Fresearch%2Fatlanta%2Fgeorgia-hotel-market-report-2025-q2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehotel%20occupancy%20is%20down%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20travel%20is%20also%20down.%20I've%20had%20riders%20tell%20me%20that%20the%20conferences%20they%20went%20to%20here%20in%20Atlanta%20this%20year%20were%20half-empty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20now%20have%20Waymo%20cars%20offering%20rides%20in%20Atlanta%20through%20Uber.%20When%20they%20started%20out%2C%20the%20fares%20I%20saw%20were%20the%20same%20as%20a%20regular%20Uber%2C%20but%20the%20ones%20I've%20seen%20lately%20are%20cheaper.%20It%20seems%20like%20Uber%20has%20lowered%20our%20rates%20even%20more.%20%3Cem%3E(Editor's%20note%3A%20Uber%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20also%20had%20to%20take%20rides%20at%20tiers%20lower%20than%20Uber%20Black%20%E2%80%94%20the%20app's%20black%20car%20service%20%E2%80%94%20because%20sometimes%2C%20that's%20all%20that's%20available.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20don't%20usually%20take%20Comfort%20rides%2C%20for%20example.%20They%20are%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eone%20level%20up%20from%20UberX%20and%20pay%20less%20than%20Black%20rides.%20Some%20of%20my%20riders%20appear%20to%20have%20caught%20on%20to%20this%2C%20however%2C%20and%20order%20a%20Comfort%20ride%20because%20they%20can%20get%20someone%20like%20me%2C%20who's%20driving%20a%20Black%20car%2C%20for%20less%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHonestly%2C%20I%20don't%20know%20what%20to%20do%20anymore.%20I%20sit%20in%20my%20car%20crying%20a%20lot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20talk%20to%20people%20with%20corporate%20jobs%2C%20they%20s